1 Setting Up

1.1 Installing Packages

pacman::p_load(sf, spdep, GWmodel, SpatialML, tidyverse, rsample)

1.2 Importing Data

1.2.1 MPSZ Dataset (Geospatial)

mpsz <- st_read(
  dsn = "data/geospatial",
  layer = "MP14_SUBZONE_WEB_PL"

1.2.2 RDS Data File (Aspatial)

mdata <- read_rds("data/aspatial/mdata.rds")

1.3 Data Wrangling

1.3.1 Splitting Training and Testing Data

set.seed(1234)
resale_split <- initial_split(mdata, prop = 6.5/10)
train_data <- training(resale_split)
test_data <- testing(resale_split)

1.3.2 Creating a MLR Model

price_mlr <- lm(resale_price ~ floor_area_sqm +
                  storey_order + remaining_lease_mths +
                  PROX_CBD + PROX_ELDERLYCARE + PROX_HAWKER +
                  PROX_MRT + PROX_PARK + PROX_MALL +
                  PROX_SUPERMARKET + WITHIN_350M_KINDERGARTEN +
                  WITHIN_350M_CHILDCARE + WITHIN_350M_BUS +
                  WITHIN_1KM_PRISCH,
                data = train_data)
summary(price_mlr)

rf <- ranger(resale_price ~ floor_area_sqm +
                  storey_order + remaining_lease_mths +
                  PROX_CBD + PROX_ELDERLYCARE + PROX_HAWKER +
                  PROX_MRT + PROX_PARK + PROX_MALL +
                  PROX_SUPERMARKET + WITHIN_350M_KINDERGARTEN +

                  WITHIN_1KM_PRISCH,
                data = train_data)
